What if the reason
we ended up here

19:13.876 --> 19:17.702
is so that you could sing
again?

19:17.805 --> 19:20.423
The music stopped!
You're laughing,
but it's meant to be!

19:20.526 --> 19:22.466
- Come on.
- It's not gonna happen.

19:22.566 --> 19:23.988
I'll cover my eyes.
I'm not even gonna look at you.

19:24.086 --> 19:25.385
Look, I'm looking at my hands.

19:25.490 --> 19:27.908
You can cover your entire body.

19:28.010 --> 19:30.193
- I don't want to sing
right now.
- Come on, Gary.

19:30.289 --> 19:31.995
- My God.
- Do you want me
to go under the table?

19:32.095 --> 19:33.716
No! Just... Stop
bringing attention to us.

19:33.816 --> 19:35.635
OK. Just do it. Really quietly.

19:35.740 --> 19:37.240
I'm not gonna judge you.

19:37.341 --> 19:39.341
Thanks, I appreciate that.

19:50.834 --> 19:52.836
OK, OK.

19:56.635 --> 19:59.903
♪ There is freedom within

20:00.004 --> 20:02.827
♪ There is freedom without

20:02.930 --> 20:05.885
♪ Try to catch the deluge
in a paper cup

20:09.173 --> 20:12.394
♪ There's a battle ahead

20:12.495 --> 20:15.356
♪ Many battles are lost

20:15.459 --> 20:18.001
♪ But you'll never see
the end of the road

20:18.100 --> 20:20.104
♪ While you're
travelling with me

20:22.187 --> 20:24.930
♪ Hey, now, hey, now

20:25.028 --> 20:29.613
♪ Don't dream it's over

20:29.711 --> 20:32.658
♪ Hey, now, hey, now

20:32.754 --> 20:36.822
♪ When the world comes in

20:36.914 --> 20:41.260
♪ They come, they come

20:41.365 --> 20:45.307
♪ To build a wall between us

20:45.408 --> 20:47.408
♪ We know

20:53.180 --> 20:55.180
That was beautiful.

20:57.783 --> 21:01.365
Clearly, it didn't work.
You're still awake.

21:01.466 --> 21:03.443
I think you should sing it
for her again.

21:03.546 --> 21:05.164
Fuck, no.
She would hate that.

21:05.267 --> 21:07.289
No, I bet she wouldn't.

21:07.385 --> 21:09.392
You don't know my daughter.

21:13.394 --> 21:16.100
-You said...
-Hey, no, no, no.

21:16.193 --> 21:19.423
The secret to the answer
is in the questions.

21:19.526 --> 21:22.305
You find out what it is that
THEY want to do,

21:22.403 --> 21:25.350
then you advise them to do it.

21:25.443 --> 21:26.408
But, then, sometimes,
I honestly have to
make up the question,

21:26.488 --> 21:27.950
because it's so boring.

21:28.055 --> 21:29.912
- You make them up?
- Mmm.

21:30.010 --> 21:32.010
- Isn't that against the law?
- No.

21:33.937 --> 21:36.999
OK.

21:37.100 --> 21:40.363
I just kind of draw on my, um,
life experience, I guess.

21:40.461 --> 21:41.966
Give me an example. You've
got to give me an example.

21:42.062 --> 21:44.283
OK.
Dear Adelaide...

21:44.385 --> 21:45.850
- Adelaide?
- Adelaide.

21:45.947 --> 21:48.854
Dear Adelaide, I, um,

21:48.952 --> 21:52.173
I feel like I'm doing
a bad job as a dad,

21:52.276 --> 21:55.017
and my little girl has trouble
telling me what she needs.

21:55.122 --> 21:57.856
So I try to make everything
perfect around her,

21:57.959 --> 22:00.026
but it doesn't seem to
make her happy.

22:00.120 --> 22:01.539
And I don't know what to do.

22:01.644 --> 22:03.062
Sincerely, G.

22:03.164 --> 22:05.385
G? OK.

22:05.488 --> 22:06.385
I can relate. Go on.

22:06.488 --> 22:09.033
Dear G,

22:09.126 --> 22:10.751
you say you're trying to
make everything perfect,

22:10.850 --> 22:13.680
but perfect doesn't exist.

22:13.776 --> 22:17.758
Perfect's the armour we wear to
stop ourselves from being seen.

22:17.856 --> 22:19.760
And maybe it's the thing that's
stopping your little girl

22:19.856 --> 22:22.883
from seeing you
and feeling close to you.

22:22.981 --> 22:25.086
Maybe you should
run towards imperfections,

22:25.187 --> 22:31.495
and laugh and cry
and dance, sing.

22:31.591 --> 22:33.254
Get messy.

22:33.354 --> 22:36.017
Messy's good.

22:36.122 --> 22:38.122
Break yourself open -
it's how the light gets in.

22:39.356 --> 22:41.363
Always, Adelaide.

22:45.086 --> 22:46.466
When did you
come up with that one?

22:46.572 --> 22:49.385
Right now.

22:49.490 --> 22:51.033
I'm trying to get you
to sing to your kid.

22:51.129 --> 22:53.555
Right...

22:53.658 --> 22:56.716
Can I ask, um...

22:56.822 --> 23:00.682
what you did in the car
for Emma?

23:00.783 --> 23:02.783
I could see
she was scared in there.

23:03.943 --> 23:06.370
She's done that before.

23:06.466 --> 23:09.533
It's like she's built this
fortress around herself,

23:09.626 --> 23:11.626
so that nothing can hurt her.

23:12.716 --> 23:14.716
I'm doing everything I can.

23:19.356 --> 23:21.461
I get scared sometimes.

23:21.562 --> 23:23.562
Scared of what?

23:25.930 --> 23:28.466
Somehow I caused all of this.

23:28.568 --> 23:31.751
After Lisa died, I spiralled.

23:31.850 --> 23:33.354
Emma was four.

23:33.459 --> 23:36.517
And, um...

23:36.622 --> 23:39.999
Took me years before I felt
like I could be her dad again.

23:40.100 --> 23:42.162
I know it probably
doesn't feel this way,

23:42.260 --> 23:43.966
but you're already doing
the best thing for her.

23:44.062 --> 23:46.606
You're present.

23:46.709 --> 23:50.171
And she may be pushing you
away, but you're there.

23:50.269 --> 23:52.372
I mean, that kind of stability
is so rare, Gary.

23:52.475 --> 23:55.336
It's... It's fucking priceless.

23:55.437 --> 23:57.459
I can't believe I just
unloaded all that on you.

23:57.557 --> 23:59.783
- I'm sorry. I am so sorry.
- No! No. No, it's OK.

23:59.879 --> 24:01.026
- I'm an advice columnist.
- Oh, God.

24:01.120 --> 24:03.664
- That's fine.
- You know what?

24:03.760 --> 24:05.260
I help everybody
with their problems.

24:05.365 --> 24:08.269
- You know what, Mary?
- What?

24:08.370 --> 24:10.591
I'm not gonna sue you anymore.

24:10.691 --> 24:11.731
No, I promise. I'm gonna call
my lawyer tomorrow.

24:11.812 --> 24:13.874
I just...

24:13.975 --> 24:14.937
I can't believe
I'm giving anyone advice.

24:15.010 --> 24:17.758
My life is a mess.

24:22.863 --> 24:24.865
Messy is good.

24:35.231 --> 24:37.238
Who put on that song?

24:39.200 --> 24:42.702
- I don't know.
- Did you just put on the song?

24:42.805 --> 24:44.747
I've been sitting here
with you.

24:44.841 --> 24:46.664
Um, I need to go.

24:46.767 --> 24:48.307
Did I do something wrong?

24:48.408 --> 24:50.908
No, I just feel like this is,
um...

24:51.010 --> 24:53.952
I shouldn't have put myself
in this situation.

24:54.055 --> 24:56.680
- What situation?
- I haven't day-drunk
in a really long time, so...

24:56.778 --> 24:58.798
I don't think it's day anymore.

24:58.901 --> 25:00.158
- Really? What time is it?
- After 6.

25:00.260 --> 25:02.260
Oh, fuck!

25:15.874 --> 25:18.376
Dear Adelaide,

25:18.479 --> 25:20.901
I've been alone
for a really long time.

25:20.999 --> 25:23.423
A boy has appeared and made
himself vulnerable to me.

25:23.526 --> 25:25.341
He has made me question

25:25.443 --> 25:27.870
why I've chosen to live
a certain way.

25:27.966 --> 25:29.834
I feel like
I'm running from my past,

25:29.930 --> 25:32.673
and I can never reveal
who I really am.

25:32.776 --> 25:34.789
I've been badly hurt.

25:34.894 --> 25:38.316
I feel lost,
and I don't deserve love.

25:38.414 --> 25:41.158
How do you know when that
person is the right one?

25:41.260 --> 25:43.260
Sincerely, M.

25:45.747 --> 25:49.008
Dear M, thank you for writing.

25:49.106 --> 25:51.691
Losing yourself - I'm not
going to sugar-coat it -

25:51.789 --> 25:54.776
that's the worst thing
you can do.

25:54.874 --> 25:57.615
Don't stop believing
in who you are.

25:57.716 --> 25:59.258
It's one thing to know that

25:59.356 --> 26:01.461
kindness and vulnerability
matter,

26:01.562 --> 26:05.624
but the first person
you need to be kind to is you.

26:05.725 --> 26:09.187
We're all feeling our way
through the dark.

26:09.287 --> 26:12.191
- Stop running in circles.

26:12.289 --> 26:14.870
Stop running from yourself,

26:14.975 --> 26:16.475
and start running to the light.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.716
Oh, fuck!

26:18.816 --> 26:22.562
Don't lose track of your heart.

26:22.658 --> 26:27.526
It's the only thing
that's keeping you going.

26:27.626 --> 26:30.048
And remember,
you don't get what you need

26:30.151 --> 26:33.091
until you're brave enough
to admit that you need it.

26:33.191 --> 26:35.894
Jump in head-first
and fight for it -

26:35.997 --> 26:37.254
even if it means
fighting for yourself.

26:37.356 --> 26:39.356
Fuck!

26:40.914 --> 26:42.740
How do you know that

26:42.841 --> 26:44.981
this person is
the right one for you?

26:45.084 --> 26:47.305
You won't know
unless you open the door

26:47.408 --> 26:49.350
to the possibility that
you do deserve to be loved.

26:49.447 --> 26:52.269
Agh!

26:52.372 --> 26:55.394
Strip away the layers
and break yourself open.

26:55.497 --> 26:58.356
That's how the light gets in.

26:58.459 --> 26:59.557
Don't lock yourself
in your basement.

27:03.376 --> 27:05.383
- Always, Adelaide.
